problem:
According to the table below, how many dollars are in the median value of the 59 salaries paid to this company's employees?

\begin{tabular}{|c|c|c|}
\hline
\textbf{Position Title}&\textbf{\# with Title}&\textbf{Salary}\\\hline
President&1&$\$130{,}000$\\\hline
Vice-President&5&$\$90{,}000$\\\hline
Director&10&$\$75{,}000$\\\hline
Associate Director&6&$\$50{,}000$\\\hline
Administrative Specialist&37&$\$23{,}000$\\\hline
\end{tabular}
solution: Since more than half the employees are Administrative Specialists, the median salary will be an administrative specialist, thus, $\boxed{\$23{,}000}$.
model_solution:
## Step 1: Determine the total number of employees to find the median position.
The company has a total of $1 + 5 + 10 + 6 + 37 = 59$ employees.

## Step 2: Find the median position.
Since there are 59 employees, the median salary will be the salary of the 30th employee when the employees are listed in order of salary from lowest to highest.

## Step 3: Identify the position title of the median employee.
From the table, the first 37 employees are Administrative Specialists, which means the 30th employee is an Administrative Specialist.

## Step 4: Determine the salary of the median employee.
The salary for an Administrative Specialist is $\$23{,}000$.

The final answer is: $\boxed{23000}$
